@NODE Install "Installation"


Please use enclosed install-skript.


If you want to install by hand, then copy the catalog ("Emperor.catalog") in the
directory "SYS:Locale/Catalogs/deutsch" or "SYS:Locale/Catalogs/français";

* create a directory called "Emperor"
* copy programfile "Emperor" into created directory
* copy startuppic "Emperor.pic" into created directory
* copy prefsfile "Emperor.prefs" into created directory
* copy guidefile "Emperor_english.guide" into created directory
* rename "Emperor_english.guide" into "Emperor.guide"
* copy scripts-dir "Scripts" into created directory (including file stormc.rexx)
* copy project-dir "Projects" into created directory (including all files)
* optionally you can copy the french or german catalog to "SYS:Locale/Catalogs/<LANGUAGE>"

Now you can use the program without an restriction.

"PROGRAMPATH:" should be the path, where you've copied "Emperor".

@ENDNODE
@NODE Start "Getting started"


The program can be started by CLI (Shell) without following arguments.

