            @{"Request-page        " link Mainwinreq}
            @{"ASL-page            " link Mainwinasl}
            @{"Locale-page         " link Mainwinlocale}
            @{"Variable-page       " link Mainwinglobvar}
            @{"Array-page          " link Mainwinarray}
            @{"Include-page        " link Mainwininclude}
            @{"Library-page        " link Mainwinlibrary}

In general the window is equal for all filing-cards.

On the left side you'll have an empty list, which should be fill by modified objects;

right from this there are some buttons:
with "Add" you can add a modified element to the own list;
with "Up"/"Down" you can move the current active entry in the own list up/down;
with "Delete" deletes the current active entry from the own list;
with "Reset list" deletes the current project;
with "Edit" opens/closes attributewindow;
with "Preview" can Emperor show, how your work looks (without compiling);

On the right side there is a list with templates for every component.



When a page is chosen, @{b}HELP@{ub} can be pressed to start the guide on that side,
which describes the specific page.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Mainwinscreens "Mainwindow - Screens - page"


This page is new since version 4.2. Here you can create screens to use in source.

Please pay attention: the prepared item "Workbench Screen" means, that the Intuition-function
"LockPubScreen(NULL)" will be called. So, just use this type single in your projects.
One screen is implemented as template: a "Workbench Screen". Surely, you can replace it by
using a "Custom Screen", whichis opening a new display (screen).
Also mixing of these two kinds is permissible.

In the attributewindow on page "Sizes" under point "Screentype" you can choose the kind
of screen, you'll generate. Possible values are following driversystems: CGX, Picasso and
original Amiga. This is available since 4.3. Please pay attention, that you have to choose
additionally the corresponding library and includes for the driversystem you choose:

@{b}CyberGraphX@{ub}
you'll need following includes:
cybergraphx/cybergraphics.h
proto/cybergraphics.h

and the "cybergraphics.library"
(choose version 40, BaseName to "CyberGfxBase", Reaction to FALSE)


@{b}Picasso 96@{ub}
you'll need following includes:
clib/picasso96_protos.h

and the "Picasso96API.library"
(choose version 2, BaseName to "P96Base", Reaction to FALSE)



@{b}HELP@{ub} can be pressed to start the guide on this side.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Mainwinwindows "Mainwindow - Windows - Page"


On this page, you are able to configure your whole windows, which do you wish to implement
into your program.

Here you must pay attention, that the current window is marked by "Active". Which means, that
the lists of gadgets depends on your current window.
I.e., ONLY the content (gadgets) of an "Active" window could be changed anyway.

@{b} !!IMPORTANT!! @{ub}

In the attributewindow you can set, whether a window should appear in AmigaOS 2.0 or
AmigaOS 3.5 - look. If you choose the OS 2.0 - look, you aren't allowed to allocate
Reaction-gadgets to it ! Also a normal window couldn't contain any GadTools-gadgets.

@{b} !!IMPORTANT!! @{ub}



@{b}HELP@{ub} can be pressed to start the guide on this side.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Mainwingadgets "Mainwindow - Reaction - page"


On the gadgets-page there are 3 groups of gadgets:


     *  On the left side there is an empty list, which later could be filled with the own
        hierarchical list of gadget-objects.
        The entries are at a time the names of the gadgets.
        An added gadget is putted into the next-higher "generation", and it's so
        an diverted gadget of the previous.

     *  In the middle are some buttons.

     *  On the right side there is a list with gadget-templates.
        If you are choosing an entry, the "Attribute-window for gadgets" is renewed, in which
        attributes can be set.


Aim of this "new" kind, to create surfaces is it to took more and more work from the
programmer. The positions und sizes are automatically rendered by the system,
in relation to the windowsize.
You can influence the arrangement of the gadgets, when you create vertical and horizontal
groups (Layouts). Gadgets, which belongs to a layout, must be diverted from the Layout-gadget,
which means that they appear in the list more right and form a new subclass.
But horizontal und vertical Layout-Groups can split into new horizontal
and vertical Layout-Groups.

Horizontal group means, that all gadgets are horizontally arranged.
Vertical group means, that all gadgets are vertically arranged.

